                                                                                                               Sleuths in the thick of things
          OUR CORRESPONDENT                              
	New Delhi, Feb. 20: The CBI today registered an FIR against B. Ramalinga Raju and set up a multi-disciplinary investigation team.         
	Apart from a battery of sleuths, five top chartered accountants and two senior cost accountants are part of a crack team of around 20.         
	The CAs have been handpicked by the apex accounting body  the Institute of Chartered Accountants of India  and the cost accountants are also from their apex body, the Institute of Cost and Works Accountants of India.        
	The charges against Raju range from criminal conspiracy, criminal breach of trust to cheating, forgery and falsification of accounts.         
	Besides, the CBI will have access to Sebi, the income-tax authorities, the Serious Frauds Investigation Office, the Registrar of Companies, the enforcement directorate and the revenue department of the Andhra Pradesh government. All these agencies are involved in probing the shenangians of Satyam founder B. Ramalinga Raju.        
	The cabinet secretariat has promised necessary support from the agencies.        
	On Wednesday, the CBI had formally taken charge following a request from the Andhra Pradesh government.        
	A five-member Sebi team today grilled former Satyam CFO Srinivas Vadlamani at the Chanchalguda jail in Hyderabad.                                                                                                                                        
